-- Boursorama Names Mercereau Chairman, CEO After Hugues Le Bret Steps Down
-- B y   V i d y a   R o o t
-- 2010-10-04T07:29:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/boursorama-appoints-mercereau-chairman-and-ceo-after-hugues-le-bret-quits.html
Boursorama said Ines-Claire Mercereau
was name chairman and chief executive officer, after Hugues Le
Bret resigned for “personal reasons.”  The company said in a statement that Le Bret has also
resigned from the company’s directorship. It said Ramon Blanco
has been named Boursorama’s deputy CEO.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net  